<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I've just noticed the boulderlings since the last patch too. I think they're a random trap spawn. Got summoned after I damaged them but was able to gate out with about half a bubble of hp's.<br>
<br>
On a side note, I lost all my buffs in that incident -- that normal?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I've noticed it a few times, actually quite a few,  we (me and a bunch of people I asked) think it happens if you actually zoned and died almost at the same time because of client/server lag...  Client and server never match up exactly, the mob landed a killing blow on the server side while your client said you gated successfully.  You come back with no buffs and the total number of HPs matches your +HP gear.<br>
<br>
The &quot;urban legend&quot; is that VI put that in to alleviate petitions regarding deaths during zoneing...  <br>
<br>
In any case, I dont claim this is the correct answer, but zoning a few times with my rogue and looking at her HPs and lack of buffs bears it out a little...<br>
<br>
