</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthinkerxvii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thinker XVII</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/26/02 4:08:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=346.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading in The Grey?</span><hr size=1> if you zone with less hp than your gear has, you lose your buffs (and dots) and appear on the other side with the hp your gear had. I used to powerlevel my twinks in befallen by just zoning out every time my hp got below my gear's hp (which was the majority of my hp). Then Id automatically get most of my hp back and any dots removed. If you actually die while zoning due to a dot, or perhaps being killed on the client but not the server or something, I think you get dropped at the safe spot as well.<br>
<br>
I swear the grey changes every week. Always new kinds of traps showing up, and mobs not popping in what used to be great soloing spots.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umelegaunt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Melegaunt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/02 12:06:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=346.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.public.iastate.edu/~eckerman/KOTG/pics/familiarface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading in The Grey?</span><hr size=1> I love this zone...it's dangerous enough that most won't use it and the exp is nice.  Some things that I've picked up from quadding here:<br>
<br>
1.  Quad with one type of mob<br>
2.  If you get adds run them away from the area you are quadding and gate (hopefully having bound in Seru or SD)<br>
3.  Keep levitate up, it will get you some space in tight places (those boulders are a pain)<br>
4.  Always zone in with invis up, you never know what someone just dumped at the zone line (they won't wander off)<br>
<br>
At 55 I have no trouble finishing off my quads here. <p><p><CENTER><IMG SRC="http://personal.msy.bellsouth.net/~dentont/eqpics/Melegaunt.gif">
